Kleinfelder is seeking a mid-level Wetland/Permitting Professional to join our Bridgeport, WV office.

Under the supervision of senior level staff, the successful candidate will lead field teams in the completion of wetland delineations, sampling, inspection, and provide technical support for a variety of projects primarily in the energy sector (power, oil & gas). The work will involve a combination of office and field work and will include developing permit applications on behalf of clients.

The position may also include assisting other senior biologists in conducting environmental impact assessments, wetland mitigation monitoring, endangered species surveys, habitat assessments, and other permit preparation.

The ideal candidate should demonstrate:
Previous experience conducting wetland delineations in accordance with USACE and state protocols. Plant identification, wildlife identification, and soils identification is required;
Ability to prepare technical documents, perform calculations, and conduct analyses;
Ability to use GIS to generate mapping and other project deliverables;
Possess excellent technical writing and verbal communication skills;
Excellent planning and organizational skills with strong problem solving abilities and analytical skills;
Demonstrate knowledge of state and federal environmental laws and regulations pertaining to energy projects;
Ability to conduct work year round in adverse climate and field conditions;
Ability to prioritize effort and effectively be engaged on multiple projects at one time
All candidates require:
BS in an Environmental, Biological or Ecological Science, or Environmental Policy; Masters in a relevant Biological field of study is a plus;
3 to 6 years of relevant wetland delineation experience;
Ability to work flexible work schedules and availability to meet priority deadlines outside of normal working hours;
Ability to travel (mostly PA, WV, and OH) with short notice up to 75 percent for field work, client meetings, agency coordination activities, etc.;
A valid driver’s license;
Experience with Trimble GPS and ArcGIS

This position provides a great opportunity for qualified professionals who are self-starters and energetic and enthusiastic leaders. The selected candidate will work with an outstanding group of professionals in both collecting field data and assisting in permit preparation.


